The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, August 03, 2004 				 Animation needs skilled hands
 ALOKANANDA GHOSH																								Calcutta, Aug. 2: The demand for skilled professionals in the animation industry is rising. 																								Currently, only 3000 animators work in various studios in the country. Industry estimates suggest that there is an immediate need for 10,000 professionals, Toonz creative director Atul Rao said.																								Content development and animation are increasingly becoming an important part of the gaming, architecture, education and medical industry. It is estimated that there will be a demand for 3,00,000 professionals in the next four years, he added.																								A study by Anderson Consulting estimates that around $2 billion worth of animation work could flow into India in the next three years. The firm pegs the animation industry at $550 million, growing at an annual rate of 30 per cent and estimated to reach $15 billion by 2008. The industry also offers scope for employment.																								Globally, the animation industry is estimated at $45 billion and may reach the $70-billion mark next year.																								Nasscom puts the countrys animation and digital media industry at $600 million and predicts that it will reach $5 billion by 2008. 
